5	
6	# Copilot Session Provider Apparatus
7	
8	## Summary
9	
10	Add a new apparatus package `@shardworks/copilot-apparatus` (plugin id: `copilot`) that implements `AnimatorSessionProvider` using the GitHub Models REST API. The provider calls the OpenAI-compatible chat completions endpoint, runs an in-process agentic tool-call loop when tools are supplied, supports streaming via SSE, and is activated by setting `guild.json["animator"]["sessionProvider"] = "copilot"`.
11	
12	## Current State
13	
14	The Animator (`packages/plugins/animator/src/animator.ts`) resolves a session provider at animate-time via:
15	
16	```typescript
17	function resolveProvider(config: AnimatorConfig): AnimatorSessionProvider {
18	  const pluginId = config.sessionProvider ?? 'claude-code';
19	  return guild().apparatus<AnimatorSessionProvider>(pluginId);
20	}
21	```
22	
23	Today, `claude-code` is the only provider. It spawns the `claude` CLI binary in autonomous mode, parses NDJSON output, and injects tools via an in-process MCP HTTP server. The `AnimatorSessionProvider` interface (from `packages/plugins/animator/src/types.ts`) is fully provider-agnostic ŌĆö it makes no assumptions about process spawning, CLI flags, or MCP.
24	
25	The claude-code package (`packages/plugins/claude-code/`) exports a `Plugin` with:
26	- `apparatus.requires: []`
27	- `apparatus.provides`: an `AnimatorSessionProvider` object
28	- `apparatus.start()`: no-op
29	
30	No copilot-related code exists anywhere in the repository. No existing files need modification ŌĆö the Animator discovers providers dynamically via `guild().apparatus(pluginId)`.
31	
32	## Requirements
33	
34	- R1: The package `@shardworks/copilot-apparatus` must exist at `packages/plugins/copilot/` with a valid `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, and `src/index.ts` that exports a `Plugin` whose `apparatus.provides` satisfies `AnimatorSessionProvider`.
35	- R2: The provider's `name` property must be `'copilot'`.
36	- R3: When `launch()` is called, the provider must call the GitHub Models REST API chat completions endpoint (`https://models.inference.ai.azure.com/chat/completions` by default, configurable) with the model from `config.model` passed through directly.
37	- R4: The provider must authenticate using a Bearer token read from the environment variable named by `CopilotConfig.tokenEnvVar` (default: `GITHUB_TOKEN`). When the env var is missing or empty, `launch()` must throw with a message naming the expected env var.
38	- R5: The provider must build the API request messages array from `config.systemPrompt` (as a `system` role message) and `config.initialPrompt` (as a `user` role message). Either may be absent.
39	- R6: When `config.tools` has entries, the provider must convert each `ResolvedTool` to the OpenAI function tool format (using `z.toJSONSchema()` for the params schema) and include them in the API request's `tools` array.
40	- R7: When the API response contains `tool_calls`, the provider must execute an agentic loop: parse each tool call, look up the tool by name in the `config.tools` array, validate arguments via `definition.params.parse()`, call `definition.handler()`, and send results back as `tool` role messages. The loop repeats until the model returns a response with no `tool_calls` or the iteration limit is reached.
41	- R8: Tool handler errors must be caught and returned to the model as tool result messages with the error description ŌĆö not session failures.
42	- R9: The agentic loop must enforce a configurable maximum iteration limit (`CopilotConfig.maxToolRounds`, default: 50). When the limit is reached, the session must complete with `status: 'completed'` using the last available response.
43	- R10: When `config.streaming` is true, the provider must use the streaming API (`stream: true`), parse SSE `data:` lines, and yield `SessionChunk` objects in real time. Text content yields `{ type: 'text', text }` chunks. Tool calls yield `{ type: 'tool_use', tool: name }` chunks. Tool results yield `{ type: 'tool_result', tool: toolCallId }` chunks. Streaming must work throughout the agentic loop ŌĆö chunks stream during each API call, pause during tool execution, and resume on the next call.
44	- R11: When `config.streaming` is false (or undefined), the provider must use the non-streaming API (`stream: false`) and return empty chunks.
45	- R12: The provider must accumulate token usage (inputTokens, outputTokens) by summing across all API calls in the session. `costUsd` must be left `undefined`.
46	- R13: `providerSessionId` must be set to the `id` field from the last API response (e.g. `chatcmpl-abc123`).
47	- R14: The transcript must contain the full message array built during the session ŌĆö each OpenAI-format message object (with `role`, `content`, `tool_calls`, `tool_call_id`) as one `TranscriptMessage` entry.
48	- R15: The `output` field must contain the text content of the last assistant message that has no `tool_calls`. If no such message exists, `output` is `undefined`.
49	- R16: `exitCode` must be `0` for successful API completion, `1` for any API error or network failure.
50	- R17: `config.conversationId` must be ignored (conversation resume is not supported).
51	- R18: `config.cwd` and `config.environment` must be ignored (no subprocess).
52	- R19: The apparatus must read `CopilotConfig` from `guild().guildConfig().copilot` at `start()` time and cache it. `GuildConfig` must be augmented via module declaration.
53	- R20: A `docs/architecture/apparatus/copilot.md` file must exist following the apparatus documentation template.
54	- R21: The package must have tests covering: successful single-turn completion, agentic tool-call loop, streaming chunk emission, API error handling, missing token error, max tool rounds enforcement, and token usage accumulation.
55	
56	## Design
57	
58	### Type Changes
59	
60	**New file: `packages/plugins/copilot/src/index.ts`**
61	
62	```typescript
63	import type { Plugin, StartupContext } from '@shardworks/nexus-core';
64	import type {
65	  AnimatorSessionProvider,
66	  SessionProviderConfig,
67	  SessionProviderResult,
68	  SessionChunk,
69	  TokenUsage,
70	  TranscriptMessage,
71	} from '@shardworks/animator-apparatus';
72	import type { ResolvedTool } from '@shardworks/tools-apparatus';
73	import { z } from 'zod';
74	
75	// ŌöĆŌöĆ Config types ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ
76	
77	/** Plugin configuration stored at guild.json["copilot"]. */
78	export interface CopilotConfig {
79	  /**
80	   * Chat completions API endpoint URL.
81	   * Default: 'https://models.inference.ai.azure.com'
82	   */
83	  apiEndpoint?: string;
84	  /**
85	   * Name of the environment variable holding the API bearer token.
86	   * Default: 'GITHUB_TOKEN'
87	   */
88	  tokenEnvVar?: string;
89	  /**
90	   * Maximum number of tool-call rounds in the agentic loop.
91	   * When reached, the session completes with the last available response.
92	   * Default: 50
93	   */
94	  maxToolRounds?: number;
95	}
96	
97	// GuildConfig module augmentation
98	declare module '@shardworks/nexus-core' {
99	  interface GuildConfig {
100	    copilot?: CopilotConfig;
101	  }
102	}
103	
104	// ŌöĆŌöĆ Internal types ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ
105	
106	/** OpenAI-compatible chat completion message. */
107	interface ChatMessage {
108	  role: 'system' | 'user' | 'assistant' | 'tool';
109	  content: string | null;
110	  tool_calls?: ToolCall[];
111	  tool_call_id?: string;
112	}
113	
114	/** OpenAI-compatible tool call from an assistant response. */
115	interface ToolCall {
116	  id: string;
117	  type: 'function';
118	  function: {
119	    name: string;
120	    arguments: string;
121	  };
122	}
123	
124	/** OpenAI-compatible function tool definition for the API request. */
125	interface ToolDef {
126	  type: 'function';
127	  function: {
128	    name: string;
129	    description: string;
130	    parameters: Record<string, unknown>;
131	  };
132	}
133	
134	/** OpenAI-compatible chat completion response (non-streaming). */
135	interface ChatCompletionResponse {
136	  id: string;
137	  choices: Array<{
138	    message: {
139	      role: 'assistant';
140	      content: string | null;
141	      tool_calls?: ToolCall[];
142	    };
143	    finish_reason: string;
144	  }>;
145	  usage?: {
146	    prompt_tokens: number;
147	    completion_tokens: number;
148	  };
149	}
150	
151	/** OpenAI-compatible streaming chunk. */
152	interface ChatCompletionChunk {
153	  id: string;
154	  choices: Array<{
155	    delta: {
156	      role?: string;
157	      content?: string | null;
158	      tool_calls?: Array<{
159	        index: number;
160	        id?: string;
161	        type?: string;
162	        function?: {
163	          name?: string;
164	          arguments?: string;
165	        };
166	      }>;
167	    };
168	    finish_reason: string | null;
169	  }>;
170	  usage?: {
171	    prompt_tokens: number;
172	    completion_tokens: number;
173	  } | null;
174	}
175	
176	/** Accumulated metrics across API calls. */
177	interface SessionAccumulator {
178	  transcript: TranscriptMessage[];
179	  tokenUsage: { inputTokens: number; outputTokens: number };
180	  providerSessionId?: string;
181	}
182	```
183	
184	**`CopilotConfig` in guild.json:**
185	
186	```json
187	{
188	  "copilot": {
189	    "apiEndpoint": "https://models.inference.ai.azure.com",
190	    "tokenEnvVar": "GITHUB_TOKEN",
191	    "maxToolRounds": 50
192	  }
193	}
194	```
195	
196	All fields are optional ŌĆö defaults apply when absent.
197	
198	### Behavior
199	
200	#### Plugin export and lifecycle
201	
202	The default export is `createCopilotProvider()` which returns a `Plugin`:
203	
204	```typescript
205	export function createCopilotProvider(): Plugin {
206	  let config: CopilotConfig = {};
207	
208	  const provider: AnimatorSessionProvider = {
209	    name: 'copilot',
210	    launch(sessionConfig: SessionProviderConfig) { ... },
211	  };
212	
213	  return {
214	    apparatus: {
215	      requires: [],
216	      provides: provider,
217	      start(_ctx: StartupContext): void {
218	        config = guild().guildConfig().copilot ?? {};
219	      },
220	    },
221	  };
222	}
223	
224	export default createCopilotProvider();
225	```
226	
227	`start()` reads and caches `CopilotConfig`. The `config` variable is captured by closure in `launch()`.
228	
229	#### Token resolution
230	
231	When `launch()` is called, the provider resolves the API token:
232	
233	```typescript
234	const tokenEnvVar = config.tokenEnvVar ?? 'GITHUB_TOKEN';
235	const token = process.env[tokenEnvVar];
236	if (!token) {
237	  throw new Error(
238	    `Copilot session provider requires a GitHub token. ` +
239	    `Set the ${tokenEnvVar} environment variable.`
240	  );
241	}
242	```
243	
244	The throw propagates to the Animator's `catch` block which converts it to a failed `SessionResult` via `buildFailedResult()`.
245	
246	#### Message construction
247	
248	Build the initial messages array from config:
249	
250	- When `config.systemPrompt` is defined and non-empty, prepend `{ role: 'system', content: config.systemPrompt }`.
251	- When `config.initialPrompt` is defined and non-empty, append `{ role: 'user', content: config.initialPrompt }`.
252	
253	#### Tool conversion
254	
255	When `config.tools` has entries, convert each `ResolvedTool` to an OpenAI function tool:
256	
257	```typescript
258	function convertTools(tools: ResolvedTool[]): ToolDef[] {
259	  return tools.map((rt) => ({
260	    type: 'function' as const,
261	    function: {
262	      name: rt.definition.name,
263	      description: rt.definition.description,
264	      parameters: z.toJSONSchema(rt.definition.params),
265	    },
266	  }));
267	}
268	```
269	
270	The resulting array is included in the API request body as `tools`. A `Map<string, ResolvedTool>` keyed by tool name is built for O(1) lookup during tool execution.
271	
272	#### API request (non-streaming)
273	
274	When `config.streaming` is falsy, make a non-streaming request:
275	
276	```typescript
277	const response = await fetch(`${apiEndpoint}/chat/completions`, {
278	  method: 'POST',
279	  headers: {
280	    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
281	    'Authorization': `Bearer ${token}`,
282	  },
283	  body: JSON.stringify({
284	    model: config.model,
285	    messages,
286	    ...(apiTools.length > 0 ? { tools: apiTools } : {}),
287	    stream: false,
288	  }),
289	});
290	```
291	
292	When the response is not `ok`, throw with status and response text. When `ok`, parse the JSON body as `ChatCompletionResponse`.
293	
294	Add usage to the accumulator:
295	```
296	acc.tokenUsage.inputTokens += response.usage?.prompt_tokens ?? 0;
297	acc.tokenUsage.outputTokens += response.usage?.completion_tokens ?? 0;
298	```
299	
300	Set `acc.providerSessionId = response.id`.
301	
302	Push the assistant message onto the messages array and the transcript.
303	
304	#### API request (streaming)
305	
306	When `config.streaming` is true, make a streaming request with `stream: true` and `stream_options: { include_usage: true }` in the request body. Read `response.body` as a `ReadableStream`, decode with `TextDecoder`, and parse SSE lines:
307	
308	```typescript
309	function parseSseLines(buffer: string, handler: (data: string) => void): string {
310	  let idx: number;
311	  while ((idx = buffer.indexOf('\n')) !== -1) {
312	    const line = buffer.slice(0, idx).trim();
313	    buffer = buffer.slice(idx + 1);
314	    if (line.startsWith('data: ')) {
315	      const data = line.slice(6);
316	      if (data === '[DONE]') continue;
317	      handler(data);
318	    }
319	  }
320	  return buffer;
321	}
322	```
323	
324	Each parsed chunk is a `ChatCompletionChunk`. Process it:
325	- When `delta.content` is a non-empty string, yield `{ type: 'text', text: delta.content }` and write to stderr (matching claude-code's real-time visibility behavior).
326	- When `delta.tool_calls` is present, accumulate tool call fragments by index. When a tool call includes an `id` and `function.name`, yield `{ type: 'tool_use', tool: name }`.
327	- When `usage` is present (final chunk with `stream_options.include_usage`), add to accumulator.
328	
329	After the stream completes, reconstruct the full assistant message from accumulated deltas, push it to messages and transcript.
330	
331	#### Agentic tool-call loop
332	
333	After each API response (streaming or non-streaming), check if the assistant message has `tool_calls`:
334	
335	```
336	round = 0
337	maxRounds = config.maxToolRounds ?? 50
338	
339	loop:
340	  if no tool_calls on the last assistant message ŌåÆ break
341	  if round >= maxRounds ŌåÆ break
342	  round++
343	
344	  for each tool_call:
345	    look up tool by name in the tools map
346	    if not found ŌåÆ result = "Error: Unknown tool: {name}"
347	    else:
348	      try:
349	        parsed = tool.definition.params.parse(JSON.parse(tool_call.function.arguments))
350	        rawResult = await tool.definition.handler(parsed)
351	        result = typeof rawResult === 'string' ? rawResult : JSON.stringify(rawResult, null, 2)
352	      catch (err):
353	        result = "Error: {err.message}"
354	
355	    push { role: 'tool', content: result, tool_call_id: tool_call.id } to messages and transcript
356	    yield { type: 'tool_result', tool: tool_call.id } chunk (if streaming)
357	
358	  make next API call (streaming or non-streaming based on config.streaming)
359	  process response as above
360	```
361	
362	When the loop exits due to `maxRounds`, the session still completes normally (`status: 'completed'`) ŌĆö the limit is a safety valve, not an error.
363	
364	#### Result construction
365	
366	After the loop finishes:
367	
368	```typescript
369	function extractOutput(messages: ChatMessage[]): string | undefined {
370	  for (let i = messages.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
371	    const msg = messages[i]!;
372	    if (msg.role !== 'assistant') continue;
373	    if (msg.tool_calls && msg.tool_calls.length > 0) continue;
374	    if (msg.content) return msg.content;
375	  }
376	  return undefined;
377	}
378	```
379	
380	Build the result:
381	
382	```typescript
383	const result: SessionProviderResult = {
384	  status: 'completed',
385	  exitCode: 0,
386	  providerSessionId: acc.providerSessionId,
387	  tokenUsage: acc.tokenUsage,
388	  costUsd: undefined,
389	  transcript: acc.transcript,
390	  output: extractOutput(messages),
391	};
392	```
393	
394	On API/network errors (non-ok response, fetch failure):
395	
396	```typescript
397	const result: SessionProviderResult = {
398	  status: 'failed',
399	  exitCode: 1,
400	  error: `GitHub Models API error: ${response.status} ${await response.text()}`,
401	  transcript: acc.transcript,
402	  tokenUsage: acc.tokenUsage.inputTokens > 0 ? acc.tokenUsage : undefined,
403	};
404	```
405	
406	#### launch() return shape
407	
408	`launch()` must return `{ chunks, result }` synchronously, but the work is async. The pattern matches claude-code's approach:
409	
410	- Non-streaming: `chunks` is an immediately-done async iterable. `result` is the promise of the full API loop.
411	- Streaming: `chunks` yields via an async queue that the API loop pushes into. `result` is the promise that resolves after the loop completes.
412	
413	The streaming chunk delivery mechanism uses the same pattern as claude-code: a queue array + resolve callback to bridge push-based SSE events into a pull-based async iterable.
414	
